!/bin/bash
Echo “hello world”

i to insert into text editor
Esc :wq
Esc: syntax on
Esc: :q!    (no save or write to close out)
Esc: u    (undo)
Esc:/html   (search for any word and n key for next)
Esc: g (gg to move top to bottom of file)
:100 (take cursor to line 100)
:set  number (gives line numbers to page file)
:s/hello/hi/g  (s for search replacing hello with hi and g is global)
:split newfile2  (Use ctrl-w to switch directions between windows)


How to edit the inside of a vim file ---  Vim /etc/httpd/conf.d/webpage.sh .


